meanings.definition: To punch harder or more effectively than someone else.
meanings.sent1: During the boxing match, the champion outpunched his opponent with powerful blows.
meanings.sent2: She outpunched her training partner in the ring, showing her skill and strength.
meanings.sent3: The superhero outpunched the villain, sending him flying through the air.
meanings.sent4: The determined fighter outpunched all his fears and doubts to emerge victorious.
meanings.sent5: The rhythmic sound of outpunched fists echoed through the gym, signaling intense training.

meanings.sent1: In the sparring session, he outpunched his rival, proving his skill and speed.
meanings.sent2: The experienced boxer outpunched the newcomer, demonstrating years of training.
meanings.sent3: The robot outpunched all other contenders in the boxing match, surprising everyone.
meanings.sent4: Her determination outpunched any obstacles that came her way, leading to success.
meanings.sent5: The champion outpunched all expectations, showing true dedication to the sport.
